{"title_page": "Yemen at the 2018 Asian Games", "text_new": "{{Infobox country at games\n| NOC          = YEM\n| NOCname      = [[Yemen Olympic Committee]]\n| oldcode      = \n| year         = 2018\n| date         = {{Start date|18|8||df=y}} \u2013 {{End date|2|9||df=y}} \n| games        = Asian Games\n| location     = [[Jakarta]] and [[Palembang]]\n| competitors  = 31\n| sports       = 10\n| flagbearer   = \n| officials    = \n| gold         = \n| silver       = \n| bronze       = \n| rank         = \n| appearances  = auto\n| seealso      = {{flagicon|North Yemen}} [[North Yemen]] ([[North Yemen at the 1982 Asian Games|1982]] \u2022 [[North Yemen at the 1986 Asian Games|1986]])<br />{{flagicon|South Yemen}} [[South Yemen]] ([[South Yemen at the 1982 Asian Games|1982]])\n| website      = {{URL|yemnoc.org}}&nbsp;{{in lang|ar|en}}\n}}\n\n'''[[Yemen]]''' participated in the '''[[2018 Asian Games]]''' in [[Jakarta]] and [[Palembang]], [[Indonesia]] from 18 August to 2 September 2018. Yemen has participated seven times at the Games since [[1990 Asian Games|1990 Beijing]], and collected 2 bronze medals this far.<ref>{{cite web |title=Participants: Yemen |url=https://asiangames2018.id/participants/country/yemen |publisher=Asian Games 2018 |accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |script-title=ar:\u0627\u0644\u064a\u0645\u0646 \u062a\u0634\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0641\u064a \u062f\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0633\u064a\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u063a\u064a\u0627\u0628 \u0643\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u062f\u0645 |url=http://www.almashhadalaraby.com/news/40212 |publisher=\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u0647\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a |date=17 August 2018 |accessdate=4 January 2019 |language=ar}}</ref>\n\n== Competitors ==\nYemen participated in ten sporting events with a total 31 competitors. Six athletes (Abdulelah Mones, Ahmed Ayash, [[Ali Khousrof]], Hussein Al-Jarrah, Salem Mohammed, and [[Zeyad Mater]]) competed in two sporting events. The following is a list of the number of competitors representing Yemen that participated at the Games:<ref>{{cite web|title=18th Asian Games: Participants |url=http://www.ocagames.com/orb/participants.php?id_game_edition=4|publisher=[[Olympic Council of Asia]] |access-date=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! width=200|Sport !! width=60|Men !! width=60|Women !! width=60|Total\n|-\n| align=left|[[Athletics at the 2018 Asian Games|Athletics]]\n| 3 || 2 || 5\n|-\n| align=left|[[Ju-jitsu at the 2018 Asian Games|Ju-jitsu]]\n| 4 || 0 || 4\n|-\n| align=left|[[Judo at the 2018 Asian Games|Judo]]\n| 4 || 0 || 4\n|-\n| align=left|[[Karate at the 2018 Asian Games|Karate]]\n| 3 || 0 || 3\n|-\n| align=left|[[Kurash at the 2018 Asian Games|Kurash]]\n| 4 || 0 || 4\n|-\n| align=left|[[Swimming at the 2018 Asian Games|Swimming]]\n| 1 || 1 || 2\n|-\n| align=left|[[Table tennis at the 2018 Asian Games|Table tennis]]\n| 5 || 0 || 5\n|-\n| align=left|[[Taekwondo at the 2018 Asian Games|Taekwondo]]\n| 2 || 0 || 2\n|-\n| align=left|[[Wrestling at the 2018 Asian Games|Wrestling]]\n| 4 || 0 || 4\n|-\n| align=left|[[Wushu at the 2018 Asian Games|Wushu]]\n| 4 || 0 || 4\n|-\n! Total || 34 || 3 || 37\n|}\n\n== Athletics ==\n{{main article|Athletics at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\nYemen entered five athletes (3 men's and 2 women's) to participate in the athletics competition at the Games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Official Result Book Athletics |url=http://www.ocagames.com/orb/files/4/62/AG2018_OfficialResultBook_Athletics_v1.1.pdf |publisher=[[Olympic Council of Asia]] |date=30 August 2018 |accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Ju-jitsu ==\n{{Main article|Ju-jitsu at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\n{{smalldiv|1=<nowiki/>\n'''Key''':\n* ADV \u2013 Won by advantages.\n* RDC \u2013 Won by referee decision.\n* SUB \u2013 Won by submission.\n}}\n;Men\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:90%;text-align:center\n!rowspan=\"